<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="973" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d973">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/3659</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Attorney General</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GTW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gregory</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-20">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 20, 1916</hi>
                                </date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department is in receipt to-day of a
                            cablegram from the United States Attorney for the District of Porto
                            Rico, as follows:</p>
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>Reported to me that Germans here have made statement that the three
                                ships in harbor here would be disabled if relations are broken off.
                                I think there is ground for believing this. Can you cable authority
                                to marshal to appoint special deputies if necessary? Marshal joins
                                in request.</p>
                        </quote>
                        <p>The Department has cabled to him the following reply:</p>
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>So far as may be necessary to protect vessels in custody of the
                                court, marshal is authorized to appoint special deputies.</p>
                        </quote>
                        <p>Respectfully,</p>
                        <closer>For the Attorney General: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <persName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Warren</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>